<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-02T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-02T07:00:00-05:00" n="556" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_VDW1">Vikner</persName>, <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_NAE1">Nyhus</persName>, et al/18:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1" type="from">Adams</persName>) to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-02T20:00:00+08:00">July 2, 1932—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 2—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>76. My 75, July 2, 3 p.m.<note n="66" xml:id="d556fn66">Not
                                printed.</note>
                            <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_VDW1">Vikner</persName> and <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_NAE1">Nyhus</persName> were released on July
                            1st at Hsiatien, Hupeh, following conference of communist <pb facs="0619" n="521" xml:id="pg_521"/> leaders who stated that they
                            gave the captives freedom because the latter belonged to poor missions
                            and had done nothing inimical to communism. Memorandum of interesting
                            statement of <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_VDW1">Vikner</persName>
                            and <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_NAE1">Nyhus</persName> follows by
                                mail.<note n="67" xml:id="d556fn67">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Adams</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>